{
  "stem": "26765.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "Van Mackelenbergh had a hardware store in [NON-ENGLISH], and he did business dealings with the commandant.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And he finagled somehow, he gave him big discounts and good prices, maybe some things free of charge.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And in that way, he got a foot in the door and was able to visit us at Camp Vught.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "Now, when Mr.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "Van Mackelenbergh was there, he said to the commandant, you see, you see, he said, those children they don't look Jewish.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "Look how fair their skin is, and they have blue eyes.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "They have a Catholic father, and he lives in America.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this put a question mark in the commandant's mind about our background.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because of that lie, we were saved.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were saved because of the help we got from the people in Holland, and because of luck, and because of this lie.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because there were transports from Vught to Auschwitz, first to Westerbork and then to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But if we had gone to Auschwitz, like most of the children, most of the people, we would have been killed right away because of our age.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But instead, because now there was a question about our background, and about, perhaps, our father being in America, we were-- we had a privileged status in the eyes of the Germans.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were placed in a barrack with a privileged group of Jews, the diamond cutters of Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They wanted to save the diamond cutters because of their skills, for, for a while, to exploit their skills.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were placed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We saw the other transports go, and that was one of my sad experiences in Vught.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
